# infra/cluster/.env.example — copy to infra/cluster/.env (gitignored) and fill
# in what you need. Loaded by every infra/cluster script via env.sh; values you
# have already exported in your shell win over this file (dotenv convention).
#
# These are the SAME variable names .github/workflows/cluster-ops.yml feeds from
# GitHub repo/environment secrets and variables. GitHub secrets are write-only —
# a local run cannot read them back — hence this file for manual runs. Store the
# canonical copies as GitHub secrets (see infra/README.md#secrets--remote-cluster-operations);
# never commit real values here.
#
# The .env file is SOURCED as shell (env.sh), not parsed: keep it `chmod 600`,
# use plain KEY=value lines, and single-quote any value containing spaces or
# shell-special characters (` $ ; \ ") — an unquoted one would execute.

# --- Scaleway API credentials (scaleway-up.sh / scaleway-down.sh) ---
# Alternative to a `scw init` profile; create under console.scaleway.com ->
# IAM -> API keys. All four are needed for a profile-less run.
#SCW_ACCESS_KEY=SCWXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
#SCW_SECRET_KEY=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
#SCW_DEFAULT_PROJECT_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
#SCW_DEFAULT_ORGANIZATION_ID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx
#SCW_REGION=fr-par

# --- Target environment for scaleway-*.sh (staging | prod; default staging) ---
# NOTE the D-26 scope guard: prod stays staging-grade until DR (Q-DR) and GDPR
# export/erasure (#90) land — bring-up is allowed, holding real user data is not.
#BK_CLUSTER_ENV=staging

# --- Cloudflare dynamic DNS (scaleway-up.sh, optional — D-27/Phase 5) ---
# Token scoped to Zone > DNS > Edit on the zone below. When set, APP_HOST and
# AUTH_HOST are required too. Unset => point DNS by hand from the bring-up summary.
#CF_API_TOKEN=...
#CF_ZONE_ID=...
#APP_HOST=beekeepingit-rc.melargil.pt
#AUTH_HOST=auth.beekeepingit-rc.melargil.pt

# --- Authentik outbound-email relay credentials (scaleway-up.sh, optional) ---
# When both are set, scaleway-up.sh creates/updates the out-of-band
# `beekeepingit-authentik-email-credentials` Secret (#361, NFR-SEC-1) that the
# authentik subchart merges into its config at render time.
#AUTHENTIK_EMAIL_USERNAME=...
#AUTHENTIK_EMAIL_PASSWORD=...

# --- GitOps repo resolution (gitops-dir.sh) ---
# An existing local checkout (offline use / iterating on both repos), else a
# shallow clone of BEEKEEPINGIT_GITOPS_REPO is made per run.
#BEEKEEPINGIT_GITOPS_DIR=/home/you/git/beekeepingit-gitops
#BEEKEEPINGIT_GITOPS_REPO=https://github.com/TiagoJVO/beekeepingit-gitops

# --- Overrides (scaleway-up.sh; defaults are usually right) ---
#SKIP_GITOPS_BOOTSTRAP=1   # skip applying the gitops repo's clusters/<env>/
#SCW_K8S_CLUSTER_NAME=...  # override the beekeepingit-<env> default
#SCW_NODE_TYPE=DEV1-L
#SCW_K8S_VERSION=...       # pin instead of "latest supported"
